Part 3
There are 3 PRs in this series: 
1) https://github.com/public-awesome/launchpad/pull/479  => Refactors the vending minter tests that will serve as the common core for other similar tests
2) https://github.com/public-awesome/launchpad/pull/483  => Create the test-suite folder where all tests will eventually go and move the two contracts affected most to the test-suite
3) https://github.com/public-awesome/launchpad/pull/486  => Shape and move all of the remaining tests to the test-suite folder

Here we move all of the remaining tests to the test-suite folder.

1)  Note that the test-suite/common_setup folder now gets a new folder /setup_minter. Setup minter has two implementations, 1) vending minter and 2) base minter. These two setups share a lot of the same code but use some different pieces where a simple code fork would make it too complex. 
2)   The main motivation of the test-suite is so that a vending-minter or base-minter with collection could easily be setup. With the help of /common_setup/templates.rs we can now do this in just four lines: 
```rs
    let vt = vending_minter_template(4);
    let (mut router, creator, buyer) = (vt.router, vt.creator, vt.buyer);
    let minter_addr = vt.collection_response_vec[0].minter.clone().unwrap();
    let collection_addr = vt.collection_response_vec[0].collection.clone().unwrap();
```
If we want to get base minter instead we can do something similar: 
```rs
    let bmt = base_minter_with_sg721(1);
    let (mut router, creator, buyer) = (bmt.router, bmt.creator, bmt.buyer);
    let minter_addr = bmt.collection_response_vec[0].minter.clone().unwrap();
    let collection_addr = bmt.collection_response_vec[0].collection.clone().unwrap();
```
3) The /common_setup/templates.rs provides pre-written setups of commonly used minter and collection configurations. If you want something that is not provided, you can just write another function that does the additional setup you need. 

4) For minter setups that don't fit in nicely with the templates approach, you have the ability to specify parameters directly. The function to call is `configure_base_minter` with a proper set of `collection_params` and `minter_params`. Here is an example: 
```rs
    let mut router = custom_mock_app();
    let (creator, buyer) = setup_accounts(&mut router);
    let start_time = Timestamp::from_nanos(GENESIS_MINT_START_TIME);
    let collection_params = mock_collection_params_1(Some(start_time));
    let minter_params = minter_params_token(num_tokens);
    let code_ids = base_minter_sg721_nt_code_ids(&mut router);
    let minter_collection_response = configure_base_minter(
        &mut router,
        creator.clone(),
        vec![collection_params],
        vec![minter_params],
        code_ids,
    );
 ```

